    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-01-29T20:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-01-29T20:00:00-05:00" n="234"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d234">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 839.00/1043.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to Minister
                            <persName type="to">Sullivan</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegrams.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-01-29T20:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 29, 1914, 8 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your January 26, 7 p.m. No objection to American going as a casual observer if
                    meetings are public but it might be resented if meetings are secret. Do nothing
                    in this matter which is not entirely agreeable to Government. Expense should be
                    small and can be paid out of contingent fund.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
